<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10107178>
    dc:description "Figs. 1–11. 1–8, Habitus, dorsal aspect; 9–11, frontal aspect.(1) Fischerotrephes jaechi; (2) Platytrephes sitesi; (3, 9) Helotrephes rompinensis; (4, 11) Hydrotrephes benomensis; (5, 10) Ascetotrephes edmundsorum; (6) Idiotrephes chinai; (7) Distotrephes zetteli; (8) Tiphotrephes indicus. (© NHMW Hemiptera Image Collection; published with permission). Images not to scale." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10107178/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10107184>
    dc:description "Figs. 40–76. Key characters of species of Helotrephini. (40, 41) Pronotal plate (pnp) and genal plate (gp), ventrolateral aspect, (44–47, 60–63) Subgenital plate of female, ventral aspect, pilosity omitted in Figs. 44, 60–63) male genitalia in lateral (left) aspect: (48, 51, 54, 57, 64, 65, 68, 71, 74) aedeagus of male, (49, 52, 55, 58, 66, 69, 72, 75) left paramere of male, (50, 53, 56, 59, 67, 70, 73, 76) right paramere of male. 42, 44, 48 – 50, Helotrephes australis, 45, 51–53, Helotrephes affinis, 43, 46, 54–56, Helotrephes flaviceps, 47, 57–59, Helotrephes rompinensis, 60, 65–67, Hydrotrephes sitesi, 61, 68–70, Hydrotrephes maculatus (redrawn from Papá ek & Kovac, 2001a; slightly modified), 62, 74–76, Hydrotrephes benomensis, 63, 71–73, Hydrotrephes langkawicus, 64, Hydrotrephes mixtus." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10107184/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

